Date: Thu 7 Mar 2019
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), 2019 [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=29767


Avian mycoplasmosis (_M. gallisepticum_), Swaziland
-----------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 7 Mar 2019 from Dr. Roland Xolani Dlamini, director of Veterinary and Livestock Services, Veterinary and Livestock Services, Ministry of Agriculture, Mbabane, Swaziland

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 13 Dec 2018
Date of confirmation of the event: 14 Feb 2019
Report date: 7 Mar 2019
Date submitted to OIE: 7 Mar 2019
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Mycoplasma gallisepticum_
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak location: Excelsior, Manzini
Date of start of the outbreak: 13 Dec 2018
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Birds / 51 315 / 284 / 284 / 0 / 0
Affected population: Broiler breeders, 45 weeks old. Population is 93% breeder hens and a couple of male birds. The farm has 2 broiler breeder sites with 4 houses each. Each site has a shower in, shower out biosecurity control. The birds were vaccinated at 10 weeks of age.

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity / Mortality / Case fatality / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Birds / 0.55 / 0.55 / 100 / 0.55
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: The disease was suspected due to the poor performance of chicks that were originating from the breeder flock in site 1. Testing of the breeder flock yielded positive results. The breeders were then put on medication for mycoplasma. Testing of all houses in site 1, as well as in site 2, is ongoing. Affected chickens in site 1 are near the end of the production cycle, and controlled culling will be done.

Control measures
Measures applied: quarantine; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); treatment of affected animals (medication with tiamulin hydrogen fumarate)
Measures to be applied: surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; selective killing and disposal

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Deltamune Laboratory (foreign laboratory) / birds / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 14 Feb 2019 / positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

